    "summary_one_sentence": "When an unexploded WWII bomb is found at a busy London construction site, military and police race against time to evacuate the area amid rising chaos.",
    "summary_short": "In central London, a construction crew uncovers an unexploded World War II bomb buried beneath a busy building site. The discovery triggers an immediate response from the military and police, who must organize a mass evacuation of the surrounding area. As the clock ticks, tension escalates among officials, workers, and civilians caught in the panic. The film follows the coordinated effort to contain the threat before the device can detonate.",
    "summary_long": "A routine excavation at a crowded construction site in the heart of London is abruptly halted when workers unearth a live, unexploded bomb dating back to World War II. The site is immediately secured as bomb disposal experts and police commanders assess the scale of the danger posed by the decades-old ordnance. With the device unstable and the surrounding district densely populated, authorities make the urgent decision to launch a mass evacuation of nearby residents and businesses. Chaos spreads through the streets as confused and frightened crowds scramble to leave while officers struggle to maintain order and control access points. Military specialists arrive to lead the defusal operation, working under intense pressure as the unknown condition of the bomb creates a constant ticking-clock scenario. Conflicting priorities between police, military, and city officials complicate the response, and communication breakdowns heighten the risk of casualties. Meanwhile, construction workers and local civilians become unwilling participants in the crisis, some trapped or reluctant to abandon the area. As hours pass, the threat of detonation looms larger, testing the limits of the emergency teams and the resilience of the community. The narrative builds toward a tense climax as the disposal unit attempts a final risky intervention to neutralize the bomb. Ultimately, the event exposes both the fragility of urban life above hidden wartime relics and the courage of those tasked with protecting the public.",
